OL,3,CGovernment U-turns on mandatory
OL,4,Cdigital ID cards
OL,6,FIn other words digital checks will
OL,7,Fstill be mandatory, but they will no
OL,8,Flonger have to be checks of the
OL,9,Fproposed digital ID cards, other forms
OL,10,Fof ID can be used too.
OL,12,FThis is what it tells us about where
OL,13,Fthe government is: Sir Keir Starmer
OL,14,Fcan turn an issue that is not
OL,15,Fespecially unpopular, into one that is
OL,16,Freally quite unpopular simply by
OL,17,Fannouncing that he wants to do it.
